consensus text: The gas given out by the action
7, & 5 of the gas produced by the action
of Potassium, upon Phosphorated Muriatic acid
Dry muriatic acid acted on by Potassium
in an exhausted retort exposed to heat
Immediately , on the lamp being applied to the
bottom of the retort , a most [deletion]in[/deletion] intense heat & vivid
flame of a beautiful orange colour, burst forth, a
peculiar red substance sublimed & coated the sides
This substance when burnt in oxygene gas
